I"1<p>Mentalising is a skill that you use in your everyday lives.</p>

<p>The term is used to describe your capacity to understand your own mental state and that of other people and how this affects your behaviour.</p>

<p>Mentalising allows you to notice and reflect on what you are thinking and feeling, aswell as being curious about what may be going on in other people’s minds.</p>

<p>Mentalising allows you to switch from concrete thought ‘She is behaving like that because’ to a wondering stance ‘ I wonder why she may be behaving like that’.</p>
